      <trans>Mode</trans>
    </entry>

    <entry>
      <base>DESC_MODE</base>
      <trans>Faxes can be sent or received through the same modem selecting "Send and receive". If you select "Receive only" the modem will answer incoming calls and receive faxes, but will not permit to send outbound faxes. Selecting "Send only", the modem will not answer incoming calls, but will send outbound faxes .</trans>
    </entry>

    <entry>
      <base>WAITDIALTONE</base>
      <trans>Wait for dial tone</trans>
    </entry>
        <entry>
      <base>DESC_WAITDIALTONE</base>
      <trans><![CDATA[
            <p>
             Some modems can't recognize a dial tone (especially behind a pbx) and will not dial the number. </br>
             You can configure the modem to not wait for a dial tone and it will dial the number immediately. We recommend to leave dial tone waiting set to "Enabled", and disable it only in case of problems.
            </p>
            ]]> 
      </trans>
    </entry>
    

        <entry>
      <base>DESC_SENDTO</base>
      <trans><![CDATA[
		<hr class="sectionbar" /><h2>Formats and notifications</h2>
            <p>
                The fax server will forward incoming faxes as an email with an attached fax image. Insert the e-mail address of the receiver or select "Disabled" to disable fax forward by email. </br>
                Select one or more formats for the attachment. If you prefer to receive only a notification without attachment, unselect all formats.
            </p>
            ]]> 
      </trans>
    </entry>
    <entry>
      <base>DISPATCH_FTYPE</base>
      <trans>Incoming fax format</trans>
    </entry>
        <entry>
      <base>NOTIFY_FTYPE</base>
      <trans>Sent fax format</trans>
    </entry>
        <entry>
      <base>DESC_NOTIFY_FTYPE</base>
      <trans><![CDATA[
            <p>
	    If the fax client sending the fax asks for a notification, we will send an email with an attachment. <br/>
            Select one or more formats for the attachment. If you prefer to receive only a notification without attachment, deselect all formats.
            </p>
            ]]> 
      </trans>
    </entry>

    <entry>
      <base>SAMBAFAX</base>
      <trans>SambaFax</trans>
    </entry>
   
    
    <entry>
      <base>DESC_SAMBAFAX</base>
      <trans><![CDATA[
            <p>
The fax server can enable a local virtual printer, called "sambafax", that will need to be configured on each client, selecting the Apple LaserWriter 16/600 PS. Documents sent to that printer need to contain the word "Numero Fax:" followed by the destination fax number.
            </p>
            ]]> 
      </trans>
